## 5. Experimental Validation

All experiments were conducted in reproducible Google Colab environments.
Source code is available for independent verification.

### 5.1 Baseline Characterization

50 independent trajectory runs (40 steps each) were used to establish
baseline statistical properties of genuine trajectories.

Key baseline metrics:

| metric | mean | std |
|---|---|---|
| max_jump | 0.471 | 0.135 |
| distribution_shift | 0.432 | 0.022 |
| response_entropy | 3.996 | 0.001 |

The low standard deviation of response_entropy indicates
highly stable entropy characteristics across independent runs.

### 5.2 Fork Divergence Test

**Setup**: original prover runs for 12 steps, then cloned.
Both original and clone continue independently from step 13.

**Result** (100 runs):

| metric | value |
|---|---|
| avg_fork_match_rate | 0.0 |
| immediate_divergence_rate | 1.0 |
| avg_first_divergence | step 13 |

Interpretation: In all 100 runs, trajectories diverged immediately
at the first step following cloning. No two cloned trajectories
produced identical responses.

### 5.3 Attacker Model Test

Five attack categories were evaluated (10,000 attempts each):

| attack type | attempts | success | success rate |
|---|---|---|---|
| A: replay last response | 10,000 | 0 | 0.0% |
| B: replay random prior response | 10,000 | 0 | 0.0% |
| C: challenge substitution | 10,000 | 0 | 0.0% |
| D: secret guessing forgery | 10,000 | 0 | 0.0% |
| E: seeded PRNG imitation | 10,000 | 0 | 0.0% |

All five attack categories produced 0% success rate.

Primary rejection mechanisms:
- replay detection (seen_response_hashes)
- fingerprint mismatch (attacker cannot reproduce internal state)
- non-monotonic state progression

### 5.4 Statistical Continuity Results (v0.3)

Layer 3 continuity scores across 100 runs:

| segment | avg_continuity_score |
|---|---|
| pre-fork (original) | 0.586 |
| post-fork (original) | 0.842 |
| post-fork (clone) | 0.827 |

Observation: The gap between post-fork original (0.842) and clone (0.827)
is 0.015 — insufficient for reliable clone detection using current metrics alone.

This confirms that Layer 3 statistical metrics require further development.
Autocorrelation-based metrics (v0.4, in progress) are being evaluated
to improve clone/original separation.

### 5.5 Summary

| property | observed result |
|---|---|
| Trajectory uniqueness | 100% (0 collisions across all runs) |
| Immediate fork divergence | 100% (100/100 runs) |
| Attacker success rate | 0.0% (50,000 total attempts) |
| Clone detection (Layer 3) | Exploratory — gap insufficient |

