## Closing Note

Traditional authentication asks: *does this entity know the secret?*

IEPP asks: *is this entity still on the same trajectory?*

When replication becomes trivial, the meaningful question shifts
from possession to continuity.

Whether continuity can serve as a verifiable, forgery-resistant signal
is the central open question this protocol explores.

